Hi all,

I recently downloaded Cantera 1.5.3 for Windows. I am having trouble 
with the Chemkin format files. I get the following error in MATLAB 
when I use the IdealGasMix command.

> g = IdealGasMix('chem.inp','therm.dat','tran.dat')
The system cannot find the path specified. 
??? Error using ==> ck2cti
Error occurred while running ck2cti. Check file ck2cti.log for error 
messages.

Error in ==> c:\niveditha\cantera153
\matlab\toolbox\cantera\cantera\IdealGasMix.m
On line 54  ==> xml = ck2cti(a,b,c);

Also, I am not able to convert the Chemkin format files into cti or 
ctml. I get the following message in MATLAB

>> f = ck2cti('chem.inp','therm.dat','tran.dat')
The system cannot find the path specified. 
??? Error using ==> ck2cti
Error occurred while running ck2cti. Check file ck2cti.log for error 
messages.

But there is an empty chem.cti file that is created. I don't know 
what I am doing wrong. Can someone please help me out.

Thanks,

Niveditha
